sentences: His most notable track was "Dirty Work Going On", which was written by Ferdinand "Fats" Washington, and originally recorded by Little Joe Blue in 1966.
He was brought up in Tallulah, Louisiana, before he relocated in 1951 to Detroit, Michigan, to work in the automobile plants.
He also spent over two years in Korea, having been drafted in the United States Army in 1954.
He moved to Los Angeles, California, where he cut some records for Kent, Jewel and Checker Records in the 1960s.
His 1966 song, "Dirty Work Going On" (US Billboard R&B, No. 40), was covered by Magic Sam, and Shakey Jake Harris, and by Willie Kent & His Gents.
In 1975, he travelled to Europe to take part in the American Blues Legends tour and album recording, organised by the UK-based Big Bear Records.
Little Joe Blue recorded for various labels, including Evejim Records, throughout the 1980s.
He played at the San Francisco Blues Festival in 1974, travelled to Europe in 1982, and appeared at the Chicago Blues Festival in 1986.
